cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.DL 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it studies the dynamics of the Twitter information network and how user behavior interacts with the evolution of the underlying social network structure. It could also belong to cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it involves the analysis of a large-scale online social media system. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) as it examines the behavior of users in a social network. The paper also involves the analysis of information diffusion and content, which could place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries) respectively.
